    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">A classified encryption device performs lookups in a substitution table (S-box) during each encryption step. You discovered that these lookups leave traces in the CPU cache &mdash; a timing side-channel vulnerability known as a <strong>Flush+Reload attack</strong>.<br><br><strong>How the device works:</strong><br>The S-box is a permutation of values <const>0</const> to <const>255</const>. For each byte of the secret key, the device computes an index: <var>index</var> = <var>key_byte</var> <const>XOR</const> <var>P</var>, where <var>P</var> is the known plaintext byte (a decimal integer, <const>0</const>&ndash;<const>255</const>). It then reads <const>SBOX</const><var>[index]</var>. This access loads one <strong>cache line</strong> into the CPU cache.<br><br><strong>Cache model:</strong><br>The cache partitions the <const>256</const> possible <strong>output values</strong> into lines of width <var>W</var>. There are <const>256</const>/<var>W</var> lines, numbered from <const>0</const>. Line <var>L</var> covers output values from <var>L</var>&times;<var>W</var> to <var>L</var>&times;<var>W</var>+<var>W</var>&minus;<const>1</const> inclusive. When the output <const>SBOX</const><var>[index]</var> falls in line <var>L</var>'s range, that line is loaded.<br><br><strong>Example:</strong> With <var>W</var>=<const>64</const>, the cache has <const>4</const> lines:<br>&bull; Line <const>0</const>: covers output values <const>0</const>&ndash;<const>63</const><br>&bull; Line <const>1</const>: covers output values <const>64</const>&ndash;<const>127</const><br>&bull; Line <const>2</const>: covers output values <const>128</const>&ndash;<const>191</const><br>&bull; Line <const>3</const>: covers output values <const>192</const>&ndash;<const>255</const><br>Suppose <var>index</var>=<const>42</const> and <const>SBOX</const>[<const>42</const>]=<const>100</const>. Since <const>100</const> is in range [<const>64</const>,<const>127</const>], cache line <const>1</const> is loaded.<br><br><strong>Your attack:</strong><br>Before each observation, you flush the entire cache. The device encrypts a known plaintext byte <var>P</var> against one byte of the secret key. You then probe the cache and record which lines are loaded (<strong>HIT</strong>).<br><br>In a clean environment, exactly <strong>one</strong> cache line is loaded per observation. In noisy conditions, additional lines may also appear loaded due to other processes running on the same CPU.<br><br><strong>Your goal:</strong><br>Recover all <var>K</var> bytes of the secret key using the provided observations.</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> <const>256</const> space-separated integers &mdash; the S-box: <const>SBOX</const>[<const>0</const>] through <const>SBOX</const>[<const>255</const>].<br><strong>Line 2:</strong> An integer <var>W</var>, the cache line width.<br><strong>Line 3:</strong> An integer <var>K</var>, the key length in bytes.<br><strong>Line 4:</strong> An integer <var>N</var>, the total number of observations.<br><strong>Next <var>N</var> lines:</strong> Space-separated integers: <var>POS</var> <var>P</var> <var>L1</var> <var>L2</var> ... where <var>POS</var> is the key byte position (<const>0</const>-indexed), <var>P</var> is the plaintext byte (decimal, <const>0</const>&ndash;<const>255</const>), and the remaining values are the indices of cache lines observed as <strong>HIT</strong>.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> <var>K</var> space-separated uppercase hexadecimal byte values &mdash; the recovered key bytes from position <const>0</const> to <var>K</var>&minus;<const>1</const>.<br>Each byte must be printed using two hexadecimal digits.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\"><var>W</var> &isin; <const>{16</const>, <const>32</const>, <const>64}</const><br>1 &le; <var>K</var> &le; 16<br>1 &le; <var>N</var> &le; 100<br>0 &le; <var>POS</var> &lt; <var>K</var><br>0 &le; <var>P</var> &le; 255<br>0 &le; each cache line index &lt; 256 / <var>W</var><br>The S-box is always a valid permutation of 0 to 255.<br>Each key byte has sufficient observations to be uniquely determined.<br>At most 2 additional noise cache lines per observation.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">99 124 119 123 242 107 111 197 48 1 103 43 254 215 171 118 202 130 201 125 250 89 71 240 173 212 162 175 156 164 114 192 183 253 147 38 54 63 247 204 52 165 229 241 113 216 49 21 4 199 35 195 24 150 5 154 7 18 128 226 235 39 178 117 9 131 44 26 27 110 90 160 82 59 214 179 41 227 47 132 83 209 0 237 32 252 177 91 106 203 190 57 74 76 88 207 208 239 170 251 67 77 51 133 69 249 2 127 80 60 159 168 81 163 64 143 146 157 56 245 188 182 218 33 16 255 243 210 205 12 19 236 95 151 68 23 196 167 126 61 100 93 25 115 96 129 79 220 34 42 144 136 70 238 184 20 222 94 11 219 224 50 58 10 73 6 36 92 194 211 172 98 145 149 228 121 231 200 55 109 141 213 78 169 108 86 244 234 101 122 174 8 186 120 37 46 28 166 180 198 232 221 116 31 75 189 139 138 112 62 181 102 72 3 246 14 97 53 87 185 134 193 29 158 225 248 152 17 105 217 142 148 155 30 135 233 206 85 40 223 140 161 137 13 191 230 66 104 65 153 45 15 176 84 187 22\n64\n1\n5\n0 101 0\n0 46 0\n0 193 2\n0 82 0\n0 208 2</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-out\">1E</pre>\n         </div>\n      </div>\n   </div>\n</div>"
